==Trivia==
*In the comics, Luke Cage, known at the streets as '''Power Man''', founded {{WPS|Heroes for Hire}} together with [[Iron Fist]]. Eventually, Cage married [[Jessica Jones]] and they had a daughter, Danielle Cage.
*Luke Cage is XXL{{Ref|LC112}} and 6'3."{{Ref|LC205}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*{{WPS|Quentin Tarantino}} was once set to direct a film based on Luke Cage after the release of ''{{WPS|Reservoir Dogs}}''. Tarantino wanted [[Laurence Fishburne]] for the role, but abandoned the film due to studio insistence that [[Wesley Snipes]] be chosen instead.<ref>[http://www.blastr.com/2015-12-21/time-quentin-tarantino-wanted-make-luke-cage-movie That time Quentin Tarantino wanted to make a Luke Cage movie]</ref> 
*[[Idris Elba]] expressed interest in portraying Luke Cage before [[Mike Colter]] was cast.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/11/20/idris-elba-mandela_n_4304880.html Idris Elba On 'Mandela,' James Bond And Why He Wants His Own Superhero Movie]</ref>
*[[Eric Thomas Wilson]], who portrayed HYDRA Guard in the ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' episode ''[[Bouncing Back]]'', campaigned to portray Luke Cage in 2011 with a video pitch.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tJwZbS1d-Jg Avenger's Luke Cage]</ref> 
*Cage wearing a hoodie in his own television series was intended by showrunner [[Cheo Hodari Coker]] as a tribute to {{WPS|Trayvon Martin}}, emphasizing "the idea that a black man in a hoodie isn't necessarily a threat."<ref>[http://www.wired.com/2016/08/mike-colter-luke-cage/ Wired: Why Netflix’s Luke Cage is the Superhero We Really Need Now]</ref>
*[[Guy Fernandez]] and [[Haaron Hines]] were stunt doubles for [[Mike Colter]] in the role of Luke Cage.
*[[Christopher Markus]] and [[Stephen McFeely]] considered having Luke Cage and [[Daredevil]] appear in ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]''.<ref>[https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/avengers-infinity-war-considered-using-luke-cage-and-netflix-heroes Avengers: Infinity War screenwriters considered using Luke Cage and the Marvel Netflix heroes]</ref> Cage was later considered by them to appear during the [[Battle of Earth]] sequence in ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'', too, but his inclusion was dropped again to not make it a "character orgy."<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/29/movies/avengers-endgame-questions-and-answers.html ‘Avengers: Endgame’: The Screenwriters Answer Every Question You Might Have]</ref>

